    AtlasNode { kind: "C", id: "SEDI-PAPER-PS21-EXOPLANET-NULL", raw: "@C SEDI-PAPER-PS21-EXOPLANET-NULL = 82/298 multi-planet systems (27.5%) contain pairwise period ratio matching n=6 arithmetic at 2% tolerance ‚Äî BUT 27.5% is BELOW Monte Carlo null expectation 67-89% for resonant 3-6 planet systems ‚Üí individual matches are NOT statistically significant :: honest-null [10*]\n  => \"Source: PS-21-exoplanet-n6-orbital-ratios.md Abstract ‚Äî VERBATIM HONESTY.\"\n  => \"Source: PS-21-exoplanet-n6-orbital-ratios.md Abstract ‚Äî VERBATIM HONESTY.\"\n  => \"Load-bearing claim: HD 110067 six-planet system has consecutive ratios (3/2, 3/2, 3/2, 4/3, 4/3) whose product = (3/2)¬≥¬∑(4/3)¬≤ = 6 = n exactly; ~1.2% of random resonant 6-planet configurations reproduce this (p~0.012).\"\n  => \"Load-bearing claim: HD 110067 six-planet system has consecutive ratios (3/2, 3/2, 3/2, 4/3, 4/3) whose product = (3/2)¬≥¬∑(4/3)¬≤ = 6 = n exactly; ~1.2% of random resonant 6-planet configurations reproduce this (p~0.012).\"\n  -> FACTORIAL-UNIV-F3-EXOPLANET-FAIL\n  -> FACTORIAL-UNIV-F3-EXOPLANET-FAIL", source_file: "atlas.append.tecsl-sedi-papers-2026-04-27.n6", source_line: 528 },
